  "title": "Crawler will not read the sitemap URL",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\n*I could not find a repo for the crawler. Please direct me to that team as needed. \r\n\r\nWhen I run the crawler will not read the sitemap. \n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a crawler with `https://www.eftours.com/` as the starting point. \r\n2. Remove the startUrls param (we need the sitemap because it has more urls on it)\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/067a6734-496d-416c-bacf-089781a035b3)\r\n3. Using the default setup run the crawler. It will not find any urls. \r\n\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nNA\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nThe sitemap should be read. \r\n\r\nI used [https://github.com/algolia/404-crawler](https://github.com/algolia/404-crawler) to see if the sitemap had an issue. No issues on the sitemap were found. It was able to read the file and find all the urls correctly. \r\n\r\nI also tried to contact support but haven't heard back in over a week [https://support.algolia.com/hc/en-us/requests/645792?page=1](https://support.algolia.com/hc/en-us/requests/645792?page=1)\n\n### Package version\n\nAlgolia Crawler\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
